Title : Drugyel higher secondary school
Text : {{tone|date=December 2018}}
{{Orphan|date=May 2014}}

'''Drukgyel Higher Secondary School''' ('''DHSS''') was inaugurated by [[British High Commissioner]] for [[India]], Sir Nicholas Fenn and Education Director of [[Bhutan]] Thinley Gyamtsho in 1994.<ref>{{cite web|title=drukgyel higher secondary school|url=http://www.drukgyelhss.edu.bt/|accessdate=5-2-2014}}</ref> Aum Namgay Om became the first [[Head teacher|principal]] of the school. Since its inception, Students across [[Bhutan]]  came to study in DHSS. Nowadays, it is considered to be one of the academically best performing schools in the country. DHSS has been consistently performing good and therefore, ranked in the top ten schools in the country over many years.<ref name="school Ranking">{{cite web|title=School rankings|url=http://www.gnhc.gov.bt/absd/?page_id=337|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502232309/http://www.gnhc.gov.bt/absd/?page_id=337|dead-url=yes|archive-date=2014-05-02|accessdate=5-2-2-14}}</ref>

==Location==
DHSS is located far from the hustle and bustle of town life.{{tone-inline|date=December 2018}} The school falls under [[Tsento Gewog]] (Upper Paro valley). It is located at a distance of 22&nbsp;km north of Paro International Airport.<ref>{{cite web|title=distance between drugyel school and paro international airport|url=https://www.google.co.th/maps/dir/Paro+International+Airport,+Airport+Road,+Paro,+12001,+Bhutan/Drukgyel+Higher+Secondary+School,+Drukgyel,+Bhutan/@27.4445117,89.3095716,12z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m14!4m13!1m5!1m1!1s0x39e19dea8ef447b3:0xd52eb6c77fd85b16!2m2!1d89.423971!2d27.403794!1m5!1m1!1s0x39e1746e180c8b51:0x6b2ad423bf5f7600!2m2!1d89.332709!2d27.48485!3e0|accessdate=5-2-2014}}</ref> It is an access point to very important places in [[Paro, Bhutan|Paro]]. It lies just on the base of [[Taktsang Monastery]] (Tigers nest), which is a cliff hanging monastery 
about 900 meter uphill.<ref>{{cite web|title=taktsang monastery(Tigers nest)|url=http://www.tripadvisor.com/Attraction_Review-g321541-d581056-Reviews-Taktsang_Monastery_Tiger_s_Nest-Paro_Paro_District.html|accessdate=5-2-2014}}</ref> DHSS lies halfway between two resorts in Bhutan, Aman Kora Resort to the north and Zhiwaling Resort to the south. The school lies at an altitude of about 2511 m above sea level and within 27029’05.6" North Latitude and 89019’56.6" East Longitude.<ref>{{cite web|title=Location of drugyel high school|url=http://www.drukgyelhss.edu.bt/SchoolHistory.html|accessdate=5-2-2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120404055841/http://www.drukgyelhss.edu.bt/schoolhistory.html|archive-date=2012-04-04|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

==School campus==
DHSS is quiet place, thereby enabling the students to concentratrate their studies.{{or-inline|date=December 2018}} The school gate is in the northern end which then leads downhill by a narrow paved road. The [[classrooms]] are located in the northern end near the school gate. Whereas, student dorms are found way below in the southern stretch where the gradient is relatively flat.{{fact|date=December 2018}} DHSS shares its campus with the first [[Hearing loss|hearing-impaired]] students in Bhutan. This disabled school is mainly financed by the German NGO Star hours – We{{who?|date=December 2018}} help children, the humanitarian association of the Bavarian Television, Munich.<ref name="9school campus">{{cite web|title=our project|url=http://www.probhutan.com/e_html/schule_Drugyel.htm|accessdate=5-3-2014}}</ref> The school has an old multi-purpose hall and a football pitch right below it. The school campus is near to a local Basic health unit center.

==Education and co-curricular activities==
DHSS has been a top ranking school in Bhutan ever since its inception.{{fact|date=December 2018}} The teaching [[faculty (academic staff)|faculty]] consist of both [[Bhutan]]ese and Non-Bhutanese  ([[Indian people|Indians]]) experienced [[teachers]].{{fact|date=December 2018}} DHSS embeds students with all round qualities.{{what?|date=December 2018}} There are various co-curricular activities which can help students become a better person.{{fact|date=December 2018}} Students play [[games]] and [[sports]] during free time.{{fact|date=December 2018}} Also, they get to showcase their talents through cultural shows and dance competitions.{{fact|date=December 2018}} Students are also taught on agricultural programmes to impart basic knowledge, skills and techniques on different aspects of farming (growing common vegetables.<ref name="Agriculture Programme">{{cite web|title=Integrated school agriculture programme in Drukgyel higher secondary school ,Paro|url=http://www.drukgyelhss.edu.bt/Agriculture.html|accessdate=5-3-2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130814073942/http://drukgyelhss.edu.bt/Agriculture.html|archive-date=2013-08-14|dead-url=yes}}</ref> A group of 33 students from Drukgyel High School visited the National Soil Service Centre on 25 September 2013 to learn more about soils, its importance and sustainable management.<ref name="Agriculture field trip">{{cite web|title=Agriculture and food security as an optional subject now included in school curriculum|url=http://www.nssc.gov.bt/agriculture-and-food-security-as-an-optional-subject-now-included-in-school-curriculum.html|accessdate=5-3-2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140503152812/http://www.nssc.gov.bt/agriculture-and-food-security-as-an-optional-subject-now-included-in-school-curriculum.html|archive-date=2014-05-03|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

==Notable alumni==
Bhutanese [[actor]] Tandin Sonam passed his high school from DHSS.  He made his debut in Bhutanese film industry with his first film ''Sleeping Beauty''. The [[movie]] was played by him as a debutant actor, who is the [[protagonist]], who believes that he will meet his dream girl one day.<ref name="Alumini,Tandin Sonam">{{cite news|last=Pem|first=Tandin|title=Review of Sleeping Beauty|url=http://bhutanobserver.bt/3143-bo-news-about-review_of_sleeping_beauty.aspx|accessdate=5-3-2014|date=August 22, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140503152359/http://bhutanobserver.bt/3143-bo-news-about-review_of_sleeping_beauty.aspx|archive-date=May 3, 2014|dead-url=yes}}</ref> He is also a singer, and sang songs like "chued chued bumo" and " Yasi mey".<ref name="Tandin sonam">{{cite web|title=Tandin Sonam|url=http://www.reverbnation.com/tandinsonam|accessdate=5-3-2014}}</ref> [[Actress]] Tandin Bhida was also a student of DHSS. At 22 years old she was nominated for national film awards for supporting actress.<ref name="Alumini,Tandin Bidha">{{cite news|title=from a paro resort to national stage|url=http://bhutannews.blogspot.com/2010/09/from-paro-resort-to-national-stage.html|accessdate=5-3-2014|date=September 10, 2010}}</ref>

